# TOC Summarizer AI

**A cutting-edge browser extension to simplify complex Terms & Conditions with AI-powered summaries.**

## 🚀 Overview

The **TOC Summarizer AI** is a sleek, modern browser extension designed to cut through the dense jargon of Terms and Conditions, Privacy Policies, and other legal documents. With a single click, it leverages the power of Google's Gemini AI to provide a concise, easy-to-understand summary, helping users quickly grasp key obligations, data privacy clauses, and termination details without sifting through endless paragraphs.

Inspired by a "Tron" aesthetic, this extension offers a visually striking and intuitive user interface.

## ✨ Features

* **AI-Powered Summarization:** Utilizes the Gemini API to generate intelligent summaries of legal text.
* **On-Demand Summaries:** Manually trigger a summary for the current page with a single click.
* **Intelligent Content Extraction:** Focuses on relevant text within the webpage, ignoring irrelevant elements.
* **Concise & Easy-to-Understand:** Summaries are designed to be short, highlighting critical points in a digestible format.
* **Cutting-Edge UI:** Features a dark, futuristic "Tron" aesthetic with glowing elements and modern typography.
* **Cross-Browser Compatibility (Chromium-based):** Built for Chrome and other Chromium-based browsers (Edge, Brave, Opera).

## 🛠️ Technology Stack

* **Frontend:** React.js
* **Styling:** Tailwind CSS
* **Bundler:** Webpack
* **Transpiler:** Babel
* **AI Model:** Google Gemini API (gemini-2.0-flash)
* **Browser APIs:** Chrome Extensions API (`chrome.tabs`, `chrome.scripting`, `chrome.storage`, `chrome.runtime`)

## 📂 Project Structure

The project follows a modular structure for better organization and maintainability:


TOC_Summarizer_Extension/
├── manifest.json             # Extension's manifest (permissions, entry points)
├── background.js             # Handles extension events, AI calls, and communication
├── content.js                # Injects into web pages to extract content
├── webpack.config.js         # Webpack configuration for bundling React app
├── package.json              # Project dependencies and build scripts
├── tailwind.config.js        # Tailwind CSS configuration
├── postcss.config.js         # PostCSS configuration for Tailwind
├── src/                      # Source for Tailwind's input CSS
│   └── input.css             # Tailwind's base CSS imports
├── popup/                    # Contains the React-based popup UI
│   ├── popup.html            # The HTML host file for the React app
│   ├── popup.jsx             # React component for the popup UI
│   └── bundle.js             # (Generated by Webpack) Bundled React app
│   └── styles.css            # (Generated by Tailwind CLI) Compiled Tailwind CSS
└── icons/                    # Extension icons in various sizes
├── icon16.png
├── icon48.png
└── icon128.png


## 🚀 Installation (For Users)

To install this extension in your Chrome (or Chromium-based) browser:

1.  **Download the Repository:**
    * Go to the [GitHub repository page](https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/toc-ai-summarizer-extension) (replace `YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME` with your actual GitHub username).
    * Click the green "Code" button and select "Download ZIP".
    * Unzip the downloaded file to a local folder on your computer (e.g., `C:\Extensions\TOC_Summarizer_Extension`).
2.  **Open Chrome Extensions Page:**
    * Open Chrome and type `chrome://extensions` in the address bar, then press Enter.
3.  **Enable Developer Mode:**
    * Toggle the "Developer mode" switch to **ON** (usually in the top-right corner).
4.  **Load Unpacked Extension:**
    * Click the "Load unpacked" button.
    * Navigate to and select the **root folder** where you unzipped the extension (e.g., `TOC_Summarizer_Extension`).
5.  **Pin the Extension (Optional but Recommended):**
    * Click the puzzle piece icon (Extensions icon) in your browser's toolbar.
    * Find "TOC Summarizer AI" in the list and click the pin icon next to it for easy access.

## 💡 Usage

1.  Navigate to any webpage that contains Terms and Conditions, a Privacy Policy, or a similar legal document.
2.  Click on the **TOC Summarizer AI** extension icon in your browser's toolbar.
3.  Click the "Summarize Terms & Conditions" button within the popup.
4.  The AI-generated summary will appear directly in the popup!

## ⚙️ Development Setup (For Developers)

To set up the project for local development:

1.  **Clone the Repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone [https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/toc-ai-summarizer-extension.git](https://github.com/YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME/toc-ai-summarizer-extension.git)
    cd toc-ai-summarizer-extension
    ```
2.  **Install Node.js & npm:** If you don't have them, download and install from [nodejs.org](https://nodejs.org/).
3.  **Install Dependencies:**
    ```bash
    npm install
    ```
4.  **Get a Gemini API Key:**
    * Go to [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey).
    * Log in with your Google account and create a new API key.
    * Open `background.js` in your project.
    * Find the line `const apiKey = "YOUR_GENERATED_GEMINI_API_KEY_HERE";` and **replace the placeholder with your actual API key.**
5.  **Start Build Watchers (in two separate terminal windows):**
    * **Terminal 1 (for CSS):**
        ```bash
        npm run watch:css
        ```
    * **Terminal 2 (for JavaScript/React):**
        ```bash
        npm run watch
        ```
    * Keep both terminals running while you develop. They will automatically recompile your code and styles on save.
6.  **Load/Reload Extension in Chrome:**
    * Follow steps 2-5 from the "Installation (For Users)" section above. If already loaded, click the reload icon on `chrome://extensions`.

## 🛣️ Future Enhancements

* **Copy to Clipboard:** Add a button to easily copy the generated summary.
* **User Feedback:** Implement a simple rating system for summary quality.
* **Customization:** Allow users to choose summary length or focus areas.
* **Backend Proxy:** For production, implement a secure backend to proxy Gemini API calls and protect the API key.
* **Error Handling Improvements:** More detailed user-facing error messages.

